  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Increasing Solid Waste Diversion and Recycling in Kampala</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims at ensuring that 30% of waste is recycled in Kampala, Uganda by 2020 which can be made possible through two outputs: i.) Building the capacity of waste collectors and recyclers to undertake upkeep of recyclable materials as well as to monitor the implementation of recycling through developing a Waste Diversion tool; ii.) Ensuring that at least 4 recycling companies access green financing through development of investment teasers and linking them to potential financiers.</narrative>
  </description>
